adjectives.description: sphingine (comparative more sphingine, superlative most sphingine)

examples: For whenever she asked him how much he had written, he regularly answered 'Nothing,' smiling at her meanwhile that courteous and Sphingine smile which Mrs Aldwinkle always found so baffling, so pre-eminently 'queer'.

entries.meaning: (organic chemistry) The amino alcohol 2-amino-octadecanol CH3(CH2)15-CH(NH2)-CH2OH related to sphingosine; any related amino alcohol
